<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-08T14:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-08T14:30:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–851: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United
                                        Kingdom</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-08T14:30:00-05:00">December 8, 1951—2:30 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2844. For Gifford. Pls advise whether you raised with Eden Dec 5
                                problem election Greece vs Byelorussia to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and if so results. (<gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 567 rptd info London 905.) If not done, sugg
                                approach be made if you believe might be helpful.</p>
                            <p>To assist <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> in deciding on
                                approach other Eur cos pls advise by Mon p m<note n="1" xml:id="d67fn1">December 10.</note> if possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>